result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:00 AM DA calls cases: 22CF38, 22CF89, 22CF96, 22CF120, 22CF125 and states appearances. Defendant Anthony Tyrone Moore in court, in custody.  Attorney Karl J Kelz. in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states a global agreement has been reached and recites agreement on record. DA Kelz states case 22CF125 has not had an initial appearance. Attorney Kaupie will proceed with an initial appearance on this matter as that case is part of the Global Settlement. in case 22CF125 Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Preliminary Hearing waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial in each case. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived.  In cases 22CF96, 22CF89, and 22CF38  Preliminary Hearings waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court.  Contingent upon the defendant's plea in cases 22CF38 and 22CF89 the State will move to Dismiss and read in all counts in cases: 22CF96, 22CF120, 22CF125. Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to each count in cases: 22CF38 and 22CF89 therefore all counts in cases: 22CF96, 22CF120, and 22CF25 are DISMISSED and READ IN. Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC. Comments by parties.
Court Imposes:

22CF38-
Ct. 1- 
$500 Fine
$200 DNA + Sample 
Payment Plan Granted: first payment due on or before 12/01/2022 $50/mo evert month after or one day in jail for every $25.00 then owing, until paid in full

Ct. 2- Withheld sentence- 2 Years Probation
Conditions of Probation: 
20 Days in the Price County Jail with HUBER privileges (Defendant is given 35 days sentence credit)
$250 DNA + Sample
$268 Court Costs 
Submit to an AODA assessment and comply with any and all recommendations per probation 
Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety 

22CF89-
Ct. 1- Withheld Sentence- 2 Years Probation 
Conditions of Probation: 
$250 DNA + Sample
$268 Court Costs 
Submit to an AODA assessment and comply with any and all recommendations per probation 
Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety

22CF96- DRI
22CF120- DRI
22CF125- DRI


Appeal Rights Given
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 29, 2022 at 10:00 am.

If not already completed Defendant must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release.
Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.
 Defendant may not operate a motor vehicle unless he/she has a valid dl in their possession. 

(22CF96, 22CF38, 22CF120)

10:01 AM DA calls cases: 22CF96 and 22CF38 Defendant Anthony Tyrone Moore appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Joseph J. Kaupie appeared by video for Anthony Tyrone Moore.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz  in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Kaupie makes statements in regards to the defendant's non appearance at the last initial appearance in case 22CF96 and a preliminary hearing in case 22CF38. Attorney Kaupie request bond be re-instated and an initial appearance happen in case 22CF96. Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled. Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Preliminary hearing requested, time limits waived.  Parties make recommendations to the court on setting bond. Court orders the warrants quashed. Court sets a $3,000 signature bond for both cases as well as a new matter that has not been assigned a case number yet. Comments by parties. Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.
Return on warrant on August 23, 2022 at 10:00 am.
